## Description {#details}

This file contains the declarations for metadata subclasses.

They represent the different flavors of metadata that live in LLVM.

<Link id="l00570" /><CodeLine lineNumber="570"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00571" /><CodeLine lineNumber="571"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Transitional API for extracting constants from Metadata.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00572" /><CodeLine lineNumber="572"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="573"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This namespace contains transitional functions for metadata that points to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="574"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\a Constants.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00575" /><CodeLine lineNumber="575"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00576" /><CodeLine lineNumber="576"><Highlight kind="comment">/// In prehistory -- when metadata was a subclass of \\a Value -- \\a MDNode</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="577"><Highlight kind="comment">/// operands could refer to any \\a Value.  There&#39;s was a lot of code like this:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\code</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><Highlight kind="comment">///     MDNode &#42;N = ...;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><Highlight kind="comment">///     auto &#42;CI = dyn&#95;cast&lt;ConstantInt&gt;(N-&gt;getOperand(2));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endcode</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Now that \\a Value and \\a Metadata are in separate hierarchies, maintaining</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the semantics for \\a isa(), \\a cast(), \\a dyn&#95;cast() (etc.) requires three</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><Highlight kind="comment">/// steps: cast in the \\a Metadata hierarchy, extraction of the \\a Value, and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><Highlight kind="comment">/// cast in the \\a Value hierarchy.  Besides creating boiler-plate, this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><Highlight kind="comment">/// requires subtle control flow changes.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The end-goal is to create a new type of metadata, called (e.g.) \\a MDInt,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><Highlight kind="comment">/// so that metadata can refer to numbers without traversing a bridge to the \\a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Value hierarchy.  In this final state, the code above would look like this:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\code</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><Highlight kind="comment">///     MDNode &#42;N = ...;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><Highlight kind="comment">///     auto &#42;MI = dyn&#95;cast&lt;MDInt&gt;(N-&gt;getOperand(2));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endcode</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The API in this namespace supports the transition.  \\a MDInt doesn&#39;t exist</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><Highlight kind="comment">/// yet, and even once it does, changing each metadata schema to use it is its</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><Highlight kind="comment">/// own mini-project.  In the meantime this API prevents us from introducing</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><Highlight kind="comment">/// complex and bug-prone control flow that will disappear in the end.  In</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><Highlight kind="comment">/// particular, the above code looks like this:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\code</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="606"><Highlight kind="comment">///     MDNode &#42;N = ...;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00607" /><CodeLine lineNumber="607"><Highlight kind="comment">///     auto &#42;CI = mdconst::dyn&#95;extract&lt;ConstantInt&gt;(N-&gt;getOperand(2));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="608"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endcode</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="609"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="610"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The full set of provided functions includes:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="611"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00612" /><CodeLine lineNumber="612"><Highlight kind="comment">///   mdconst::hasa                &lt;=&gt; isa</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00613" /><CodeLine lineNumber="613"><Highlight kind="comment">///   mdconst::extract             &lt;=&gt; cast</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00614" /><CodeLine lineNumber="614"><Highlight kind="comment">///   mdconst::extract&#95;or&#95;null     &lt;=&gt; cast&#95;or&#95;null</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00615" /><CodeLine lineNumber="615"><Highlight kind="comment">///   mdconst::dyn&#95;extract         &lt;=&gt; dyn&#95;cast</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00616" /><CodeLine lineNumber="616"><Highlight kind="comment">///   mdconst::dyn&#95;extract&#95;or&#95;null &lt;=&gt; dyn&#95;cast&#95;or&#95;null</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00617" /><CodeLine lineNumber="617"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00618" /><CodeLine lineNumber="618"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The target of the cast must be a subclass of \\a Constant.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00619" /><CodeLine lineNumber="619" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/mdconst"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">namespace </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/mdconst">mdconst</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00648" /><CodeLine lineNumber="648"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00650" /><CodeLine lineNumber="650"><Highlight kind="comment">/// type \\c X.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1050"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Metadata node.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1051"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1052"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Metadata nodes can be uniqued, like constants, or distinct.  Temporary</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1053"><Highlight kind="comment">/// metadata nodes (with full support for RAUW) can be used to delay uniquing</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1054"><Highlight kind="comment">/// until forward references are known.  The basic metadata node is an \\a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1055"><Highlight kind="comment">/// MDTuple.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1056"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1057"><Highlight kind="comment">/// There is limited support for RAUW at construction time.  At construction</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1058"><Highlight kind="comment">/// time, if any operand is a temporary node (or an unresolved uniqued node,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1059"><Highlight kind="comment">/// which indicates a transitive temporary operand), the node itself will be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1060"><Highlight kind="comment">/// unresolved.  As soon as all operands become resolved, it will drop RAUW</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1061"><Highlight kind="comment">/// support permanently.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1062"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1063"><Highlight kind="comment">/// If an unresolved node is part of a cycle, \\a resolveCycles() needs</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1064"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to be called on some member of the cycle once all temporary nodes have been</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1065"><Highlight kind="comment">/// replaced.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1066"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1067"><Highlight kind="comment">/// MDNodes can be large or small, as well as resizable or non-resizable.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1068"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Large MDNodes&#39; operands are allocated in a separate storage vector,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1069"><Highlight kind="comment">/// whereas small MDNodes&#39; operands are co-allocated. Distinct and temporary</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1070"><Highlight kind="comment">/// MDnodes are resizable, but only MDTuples support this capability.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1071"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1072"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Clients can add operands to resizable MDNodes using push&#95;back().</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1073" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mdnode"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mdnode/#aa62a8f06c7c38176942b29855f33ddbc">MDNode</a> : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata/#ac265aa582f1e66e4e45d6a964b9bd303">Metadata</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1677"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Placeholder metadata for operands of distinct MDNodes.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1678"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1679"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is a lightweight placeholder for an operand of a distinct node.  It&#39;s</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1680"><Highlight kind="comment">/// purpose is to help track forward references when creating a distinct node.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1681"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This allows distinct nodes involved in a cycle to be constructed before</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1682"><Highlight kind="comment">/// their operands without requiring a heavyweight temporary node with</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1683"><Highlight kind="comment">/// full-blown RAUW support.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1684"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1685"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Each placeholder supports only a single MDNode user.  Clients should pass</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1686"><Highlight kind="comment">/// an ID, retrieved via \\a getID(), to indicate the &quot;real&quot; operand that this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1687"><Highlight kind="comment">/// should be replaced with.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1688"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1689"><Highlight kind="comment">/// While it would be possible to implement move operators, they would be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1690"><Highlight kind="comment">/// fairly expensive.  Leave them unimplemented to discourage their use</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1691"><Highlight kind="comment">/// (clients can use std::deque, std::list, BumpPtrAllocator, etc.).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1692" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/distinctmdoperandplaceholder"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/distinctmdoperandplaceholder/#af6749770ad338c5719e1f3602bd8b5ea">DistinctMDOperandPlaceholder</a> : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata/#ac265aa582f1e66e4e45d6a964b9bd303">Metadata</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
